---
import Layout from '~/layouts/PageLayout.astro';

const metadata = {
  title: 'Worldbuilding — Emjay',
  description: 'Free Pax States and the Kilumi conlang on Urth.',
};
---

<Layout metadata={metadata}>
  <section class="px-4 py-12 sm:py-16 lg:py-20 mx-auto max-w-4xl">
    <h1 class="text-4xl md:text-5xl font-bold mb-6">Worldbuilding</h1>
    <p class="text-xl text-muted mb-8">
      Building Urth — a world of fractured nations, living languages, and quiet revolutions.
    </p>

    <div class="prose prose-lg dark:prose-invert max-w-none">
      <h2>Free Pax States</h2>
      <p>
        A loose confederation born after the Pax collapse. Not a country — a network of city-states, trade routes, and
        mutual-defense pacts trying to stay free in a world that keeps centralizing.
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li>Political structure: council of envoys, no standing army</li>
        <li>Culture: maker-first, archive-obsessed, skeptical of empires</li>
        <li>Current focus: mapping the border towns and their treaties</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Kilumi — Conlang of Urth</h2>
      <p>
        Kilumi is the trade tongue of the southern archipelagos. Agglutinative, vowel-harmony, built for clarity over
        poetry — though it has plenty of both.
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li>Phonology: 5 vowels, 14 consonants, no tones</li>
        <li>Grammar: SOV, case stacking, evidentiality markers</li>
        <li>Status: working lexicon ~800 words, grammar sketch in progress</li>
      </ul>

      <p><em>More maps, lexicon entries, and short fiction coming soon.</em></p>
    </div>
  </section>
</Layout>
